We use the terms “personal information” or “personal data” interchangeably in this Privacy Policy to refer to information that identifies, relates to, describes, or is reasonably capable of being associated, directly or indirectly, with an individual. Personal information does not include information that has been modified in a substantial way so that it no longer can reasonably identify or be linked to an individual.
        We obtain personal information from a range of sources including (but not limited to) the following:
        1.	Information you submit online (including, but not limited to, filling out forms or requests on the Sites, sending us a message, or responding to our marketing messaging and promotions);
        2.	Information collected when you visit our Sites as described in the section titled, “Information We Collect Using Cookies and Other Technologies” and in our Cookie Policy;
        3.	Information provided by the fitness center you use;
        4.	Information collected during a workout session if you are an exerciser who uses our connected fitness products;
        5.	Social media accounts you use to interact with Goals;
        6.	Market research services and public and commercial resources.
        7.	This Privacy Policy does not apply to any personal information collected by the third-party source (app store) from which you download our mobile application and we are not responsible for the privacy practices of your app store. As explained below, this Privacy Policy does not apply to the privacy practices of third-party services that provide functionality for our Sites (such as plug-ins), information you post on social media, information you post or send using a messaging or other application (such as WhatsApp Messenger), or information collected by third-party websites to which you navigate from links on our Sites.

The personal information we collect is processed for the following purposes:
1.	To offer our products and services, respond to your requests and provide information and communicate with you about our products and services;
2.	To register and maintain an online or offline account;
3.	To process orders and other transactions, including warranty and product registration, payments, claims, requests, and provide customer service;.
4.	To provide information about financial options for the purchase of our products;
5.	To operate, analyze and enhance the performance and functioning of our Site, products and services;
6.	To prevent fraud; to enforce the Sites’ Terms of Use; to comply with applicable laws and corporate reporting obligations; and to enforce Goals’s agreements;
7.	To analyze how the Sites are used, to prepare aggregated trend reports, and to perform other market research;
8.	To provide you with online advertisements and marketing emails based on your interests and permissions;
9.	To facilitate your interaction through our Sites with other consumers, including through social networking;
10.	To send notices, newsletters, marketing communications, promotions, solicitations, brochures, or other marketing materials regarding our Sites, our products, and the services of our businesses, affiliates, business partners, or authorized dealers;
11.	To monitor and analyze usage and trends, evaluate and compare interest in our products and services and develop new products and services;
12.	To receive and process applications for employment;
13.	To provide our interactive console and mobile app workout recommendations to exercisers; and
14.	To provide our equipment monitoring and management services to fitness centers and other commercial customers.
Goals processes your personal information where we have a legal basis to do so. The legal basis that we will rely on will be one of the following:
1.	You have consented to our processing your personal information;
2.	The processing is necessary to perform a contract with you or to fulfill a request you have made;
3.	The processing is necessary to comply with a legal obligation that applies to Goals under US, EU or Member State or other applicable law; or
4.	The processing is necessary for purposes that are in Goals’ legitimate interests as a multinational equipment manufacturer and retailer in order to, for example, protect our business and better understand our customers.
We may use your personal information to develop a personal profile about you. We may use the personal information in your profile to respond to requests for financial options for purchasing products and services from us and to contact to you for marketing purposes.
